7.1.13 - M365SR13: Potentially Unauthorised Transfer of User Profiles to LinkedIn
ISM controls:
•	Control: 1537; Revision: 1; Updated: Sep-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Restricting user access to cloud service settings and data)
•	Control: 0846; Revision: 6; Updated: Jun-21; Applicability: All; OS: All (Authorising and restricting access to data and applications)
•	Control: 1511; Revision: 2; Updated: Dec-22; Applicability: All; OS: All (Preventing unauthorised data exfiltration via cloud services)
________________________________________
Current Risk With Microsoft integrating LinkedIn functionality with M365, there is the potential for agency user profile information to be transferred to LinkedIn and viewed publicly, increasing the risk of impact to the confidentiality of agency information.
Risk Assessment:
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
ALMOST CERTAIN	x	MINOR	=	MEDIUM
Export to Sheets
________________________________________
Recommendations:
1.	Disable LinkedIn Integration: Configure the M365 tenant-wide settings to disable LinkedIn account connections, preventing the synchronisation of organisational directory data with personal LinkedIn profiles.
2.	Restrict User Profile Visibility: Use Entra ID settings to limit the amount of directory information visible to external applications and ensure that sensitive attributes (e.g., specific project team names or office locations) are hidden by default.
3.	Update Acceptable Use Policies: Ensure agency policies explicitly prohibit the linking of corporate identities to personal social media accounts to maintain a clear boundary between professional and private data.
- Treatment #1
•	Tenant Configuration: Navigate to the Microsoft 365 Admin Centre and toggle off the "LinkedIn integration" setting for all users.
•	Entra ID Policy Review: Audit the "User settings" blade in Entra ID to ensure "Users can connect their work or school account with LinkedIn" is set to "No."
•	Staff Communication: Issue a security advisory to all staff explaining the privacy risks associated with social media integration and the agency's stance on identity separation.
________________________________________
Residual risk outcome if recommendation is implemented. By technically disabling the integration at the tenant level, the automated path for data transfer is eliminated. This significantly reduces the likelihood of accidental public exposure of internal profile details. While users may still manually update their LinkedIn profiles, the systemic risk to agency directory integrity is reduced to "Unlikely."
Risk Likelihood	x	Risk Consequence	=	Risk Rating
UNLIKELY	x	MINOR	=	LOW
